            </li>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/business-icon-6.png" alt="">
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">User data on the blockchain</p>
            <p class="words">With Distributed Credit Chain’s verification services, a user’s basic information is verified, processed, stored locally while its hash will be recorded on DCC. Therefore, personal data can be validated and used multiple times in the future. Credit Agencies are free from having to repeatedly obtain authorization from users for access to their data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">Obtain user’s data</p>
            <p class="words">When an agency wants to use an individual’s data asset, the individual will submit a personal data report and verify it by using Distributed Credit Chain’s smart. As information on the blockchain cannot be tampered, the verification process will be quick and low-cost.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">Provide credit services</p>
            <p class="words">Credit agencies can sign contracts with Distributed Credit Chain’s partnered lenders, provide risk-control services, analyze user data and provide them to lenders, who then decide whether to lend based on the results from risk-control.</p>
            <p class="words">Distributed Credit Chain provides anti-fraud and modeling algorithms, in order to help financial institutions process personal data without data storage. In this way, it helps financial institutions improve their risk control capabilities in accordance with compliance requirements.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="bottom-content content">
      <div class="title">
        <img src="../images/circle.png" alt="">Why join us
      </div>
      <div class="details">
        <div class="bg-img__join">
          <div class="left-up decorate">
            Lower costs - No need for repetitive verification, since the basic information has been verified
          </div>
          <div class="right-up decorate">
            Non-tampered information - Data stored on blockchain-based networks
          </div>
          <div class="left-middle decorate">
            Higher corporate value - Services facing multiple users
          </div>
          <div class="right-middle decorate">
            Minimum risk of data leakage - Information stored locally
          </div>
          <div class="left-bottom decorate">
            More opportunities - Connecting multiple lenders
          </div>
          <div class="right-bottom decorate">
            Compliance with regulations - Secured services meet with regulations
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div style="display: none;" class="loan-part">
    <div class="content">
      <div class="details">
        <div class="left">
          <ul>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/business-icon-1.png" alt="">
            </li>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/arrow.png" alt="">
            </li>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/business-icon-2.png" alt="">
            </li>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/arrow.png" alt="" class="arrow3">
            </li>
            <li>
              <img src="../images/business-icon-3.png" alt="">
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="right">
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">User applies for a loan</p>
            <p class="words">When a user applies for a loan on the client, the application will be placed on the blockchain, where information is public and timestamps cannot be tampered. Therefore, borrowers are unable to repudiate.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">Obtain user’s credit information</p>
            <p class="words">Loan agencies can sign contracts with credit agencies that have joined Distributed Credit Chain, for risk-control services. When individuals apply for loans, credit agencies will analyze, process and provide user data to loan agencies. In this way, credit agencies proactively select available lending services, instead of spending resources on lenders who are unable to provide loans.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="paragraph">
            <p class="emphasis">Borrowing records on the blockchain</p>
            <p class="words">Loan agencies submit to the blockchain results of borrowing applications, so that individuals’ credit records are shared with all agencies. If the loan is successfully granted, the contract and post-loan performance will all be updated on the blockchain, where information cannot be tampered, and all behaviors can be tracked.</p>
            <p class="words">With credit history reports shared on the blockchain, data approved by both parties is accessible to other institutions that need to obtain such data. This effectively prevents problems such as long-term borrowing and repeated test borrowing.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="title">
        Our services
        <img src="../images/circle.png" alt="">
      </div>
    </div>
